Durban - Prince Harry and Meghan Markle will wed at St George’s Chapel in the grounds of Windsor Castle on Saturday.  Their pending nuptials have the world in a tizz with excitement. Here are some interesting facts from the planning...        * Around 600 people have been invited to the service at St George's Chapel. All 600 guests have also been invited to the lunchtime reception at St George's Hall, which is being given by Her Majesty The Queen. Later that evening, around 200 guests are being invited to the private reception at Frogmore House given by The Prince of Wales.     * The cake: Claire Ptak, an American pastry chef who is based in London, has been chosen to create a lemon elderflower wedding cake for the Royal Couple.    (Info and pics source: www.royal.uk/royalwedding)  Daily News